<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <%= render "shared/page_header", title: "Help", size: "2xl" %>
  <%= render "shared/help_nav", current: :extension_help %>

  <section class="pb-12">
    <h2 class="text-lg/8 font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Browser Extension</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm/6 text-mist-700 dark:text-mist-400">
      Send any article to your podcast feed with one click.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-6 text-sm/6 text-mist-700 dark:text-mist-400">
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Installation</h3>
      <ol class="mt-3 list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
        <li>Install the extension from the <a href="#" class="text-mist-950 underline dark:text-white">Chrome Web Store</a></li>
        <li>Click the extension icon in your browser toolbar</li>
        <li>You'll be redirected to connect your account</li>
        <li>Once connected, you're ready to go!</li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">How to Use</h3>
      <ol class="mt-3 list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
        <li>Navigate to any article or blog post you want to listen to</li>
        <li>Click the <strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">TTS Podcast</strong> icon in your toolbar</li>
        <li>The icon shows a <strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">green checkmark</strong> when the article is sent</li>
        <li>Open your podcast app -- the episode will appear in your feed</li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Icon Badge States</h3>
      <p class="mt-3">The extension shows a small badge on the icon to indicate status:</p>
      <ul class="mt-3 space-y-3">
        <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded bg-mist-100 dark:bg-mist-800 text-sm font-medium text-mist-500 dark:text-mist-400">--</span>
          <span><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">No badge</strong> -- Ready to send an article</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded bg-blue-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">...</span>
          <span><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Blue dots</strong> -- Sending article</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded bg-green-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">&#x2713;</span>
          <span><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Green checkmark</strong> -- Article sent to your feed</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded bg-red-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">!</span>
          <span><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Red exclamation</strong> -- Something went wrong (page may not be an article)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Disconnecting</h3>
      <p class="mt-3">To disconnect the extension from your account:</p>
      <ol class="mt-3 list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
        <li><strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Right-click</strong> the extension icon</li>
        <li>Select <strong class="text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Disconnect from TTS</strong></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="mt-3">
        You can also disconnect from your <%= link_to "account settings", settings_extensions_path, class: "text-mist-950 underline dark:text-white" %>.
      </p>

      <h3 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Troubleshooting</h3>

      <h4 class="mt-6 text-sm font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">"This page does not appear to be an article"</h4>
      <p class="mt-2">
        The extension works best on article pages with substantial text content. It may not work on:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
        <li>Home pages or index pages</li>
        <li>Pages with mostly images or video</li>
        <li>Pages behind paywalls or login walls</li>
        <li>PDFs or non-HTML content</li>
      </ul>

      <h4 class="mt-6 text-sm font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Extension shows error state</h4>
      <p class="mt-2">
        Try refreshing the page and clicking the icon again. If the problem persists, the page content may not be extractable.
      </p>

      <h4 class="mt-6 text-sm font-semibold text-mist-950 dark:text-white">Need to reconnect?</h4>
      <p class="mt-2">
        If you're logged out or need to reconnect, just click the extension icon -- you'll be redirected to the connect page automatically.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
